        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Thinking Tokens and Scratchpad Format"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Models trained with RL on outcomes develop a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "scratchpad",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " — a block of tokens that the model generates before the final answer. These thinking tokens are never shown to the user (in deployed systems like Claude or o1) but are fully attended to by subsequent tokens including the final answer. The model learns to use the scratchpad for subgoal decomposition, hypothesis testing, and error checking."
          }
        ]
      },
